# Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID (JavaScript implicit flow — no secret required)
#
# How to obtain:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#   2. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID  →  Application type: Web application
#   3. Authorised JavaScript origins:  https://migraintrack.com
#   4. Authorised redirect URIs:       https://migraintrack.com/
#                                      http://localhost:5173/   (dev only)
#   5. Enable the Google Drive API for the project.
#
# The client_id is a PUBLIC identifier — safe to include in source code and
# visible in every OAuth redirect URL. No client_secret is used or needed.
# This app uses OAuth implicit flow and avoids refresh-token grant usage.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your value:
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=572277088448-1u6c9t2v8b8tba7g8ta2uma27ujald4t.apps.googleusercontent.com
